LONDON. Antonio Conte will not entertain the idea of selling Willian to Manchester United but the Chelsea head coach is willing to let fellow Brazil international Oscar leave this summer. Juventus are the frontrunners to sign Oscar, with Conte prepared to hand Juan Cuadrado another chance in the English Premier League following his successful season-long loan in Turin.Conte will take over after Euro 2016 and knows it would not go down well with fans if he allowed Chelsea s Player of the Year award winner, Willian, to join a rival club.The Italian will not sign off on the transfer, with Sportsmail told Willian s move to Manchester is a total no-go due to Conte and Chelsea s reluctance.Jose Mourinho is a fan and could try to test them with an offer, but would struggle to sign the Brazilian. Mailonline